The lifting of travel restrictions by East Germany has given new life to the idea of a  single Germany.
The recently observed 50th anniversary of the start of World War II was  a reminder of the danger posed by a unified Germany.
No one is thinking in terms of  another war, but an undivided Germany could become the unchallenged economic and  political force on the continent.
A top aide to former Secretary Kissinger says that reunification is terrifying to the  countries most closely affected.
Only the people of East Germany want it, and they will  be the decisive factor. 
